==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wood tick
<hw>Wood" tick`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
several species of ticks of the genus <gen>Ixodes</gen> whose young
cling to bushes, but quickly fasten themselves upon the bodies of any
animal with which they come in contact. When they attach themselves to
the human body they often produce troublesome sores. The common species
of the Northern United States is <spn>Ixodes
unipunctata</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woodwall</ent>⟦br⟧
